certain scripts are certainly taboo, such as the autoseiger. Yes i know, i made one a while back that could rape a guy of 20 planets in 7 seconds - and thats exactly why they aren't allowed. (ps i considered making it threaded, so if the guy blinked, he would be dead, but allas, too evil for even my programming curiousity :-P). If you use an autosieger, I will most likely delete ur account. I know i made one that was uber evil - I will not attempt to say I was innocent of it. But if it makes you feel any better, I only used it on people who had more then 400 planets :-P. And note, i do not use this script anymore.<br />
<br />
also, some scripts were poorly designed. They would invest in all the planets, everysingle turn, instead of using planet invest pool. This did put a greater load on the server. Mindwarper's stance on scripts, i believe, is that none are allowed. If you do use a script, plz have the decentcy of making it efficient. The planet invest script i made a long time ago, predicted when the funds would run out, as a result it only needed to ceck the planet invest pool every 10-20 turns, not every single turn.<br />
<br />
other people created scripts that would monitor the battle reports and automatically send allied fleets to anyone who was attack. This is seriously gay. <br />
a) it requires constant BR checking, which is bad for the server<br />
b) it is gay because it gives your council a vastly greater advantage over other councils.<br />
if i find out anyone has been using such a script, I will not hesitate in deleting their account.<br />
<br />
the last script type was the infobot. infobots are often used in irc for fast referencing. This allow ed players to simply say &quot;!pp zbyte&quot; and display his stats for example. I personally do not mind such a thing. All that is, is something to more efficiently look up data. If anything it is better for the server since instead of 5+ people looking up a player on the server, only one person's account does. I do not consider that type of infobot to give someone an &quot;advantage&quot; but rather simply make gaming easier.<br />
<br />
To me there are 3 types of scripts.<br />
a) scripts that do what the game itself should do, such as an autofleeter.<br />
b) scripts that make your life easier but don't give an advantage, such as infobots<br />
c) scripts that are lame and will get your account deleted. Autoseiger, Auto-ally-send-fleets-on-attack, message spammer, etc<br />
<br />
autoexpeditions and such is in a grey area, but i would prefer if people do not use it :/<p><br>&lt;zbyte645795&gt;	so tita, there is two of me!<br />
&lt;zbyte645795&gt;	one to pimp out<br />
&lt;zbyte64&gt;	the other to keep to urself<br />
&lt;TitaniaX&gt;	or i could just pimp both of you and get twice as much			   <P align=right></P>
